# WholesaleUp Production Standards

Reference document for migrating the WholesaleUp project from design-phase demo code to production-ready implementation. Consult this before creating API routes, replacing mock data, adding server-side logic, or deploying.

Last updated: 2026-03-04

---

## 1. Production Gap Registry

Every demo pattern in the codebase is tracked here. When fixing a gap, mark it `✅ DONE` with the date. Items are ordered by severity within each category.

### 1.1 CRITICAL — Security & Data Integrity

These MUST be resolved before any public deployment.

| # | File(s) | Gap | Demo Pattern | Production Fix |
|---|---------|-----|-------------|----------------|
| C1 | `use-recaptcha.js:19` | Hardcoded test reCAPTCHA key | Google's public test key `6LeIxAcT...` | Use `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY` |
| C2 | `use-recaptcha.js` | No server-side token verification | Token generated but never verified | Create `POST /api/verify-recaptcha` with secret key + score threshold (≥ 0.5) |
| C3 | `next.config.js:21` | `'unsafe-inline'` + `'unsafe-eval'` in CSP | Allows arbitrary inline scripts | Implement nonce-based CSP; remove `unsafe-eval` |
| C4 | `next.config.js:69-73` | HSTS header commented out | Disabled pending SSL | Enable `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains` |
| C5 | `auth.js:38-57` | No database persistence for OAuth | JWT callbacks don't write to DB | Add user table; persist profile on first sign-in; merge provider data |
| C6 | `auth.js` | No session revocation | No way to invalidate sessions | Implement session table + token blacklist |
| C7 | `use-rate-limit.js` | Client-side only rate limiting | localStorage-based counters | Implement server-side rate limiting (Redis/Upstash or database) per IP + email |
| C8 | `middleware.ts:13` | Plaintext password site protection | Basic auth with `SITE_PASSWORD` env | Replace with proper auth (JWT/OAuth) or remove for public launch |
| C9 | `register.jsx:186`, `auth-modal.jsx` | `demo-auth` CustomEvent pattern | `window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("demo-auth", ...))` | Replace with real NextAuth session state via `useSession()` |
| C10 | `register.jsx`, `auth-modal.jsx` | Login uses `Math.random()` outcomes | `setTimeout` + random roll simulates success/fail | Call `signIn("credentials", {...})` via NextAuth |
| C11 | `register.jsx:428`, `auth-modal.jsx` | Register uses `setTimeout` success | 1.8s timeout → mark success | POST to `/api/auth/register` (hash password, create user, return session) |
| C12 | `use-verification-email.js:31-44` | Email sending is simulated | `setTimeout` + console.log | Integrate real email service (SendGrid/Resend/SES); create verification token system |
| C13 | `use-email-check.js:39-43` | Email check uses demo data | `REGISTERED_EMAILS` Set + `setTimeout` | Create `GET /api/auth/check-email` querying real database |
| C14 | `use-username-check.js:46-50` | Username check uses demo data | `TAKEN_USERNAMES` Set + `setTimeout` | Create `GET /api/auth/check-username` querying real database |
| C15 | `contact.jsx:539-549` | Contact form submission simulated | `setTimeout` → mark success | POST to `/api/contact` (validate, sanitize, send email, store in DB) |
| C16 | Dashboard, single-deal, supplier-profile pages | No auth gating | Pages render without checking login | Add auth checks via middleware or `useSession()`; redirect unauthenticated users |

### 1.2 HIGH — Core Functionality

Must be resolved for the platform to function with real data.

| # | File(s) | Gap | Production Fix |
|---|---------|-----|----------------|
| H1 | All phase components | Hardcoded mock data arrays | Replace with database queries via API routes or Server Components |
| H2 | All `page.tsx` files | No server-side data fetching | Convert to async Server Components; fetch data before render |
| H3 | No `error.tsx` files | Missing error boundaries | Create `error.tsx` at each route level with user-friendly messages |
| H4 | No `loading.tsx` files | Missing loading skeletons | Create `loading.tsx` at each data-dependent route |
| H5 | `auth-modal.jsx`, `register.jsx` | Forgot password is simulated | Create `POST /api/auth/forgot-password` (generate token, send email, always return success) |
| H6 | `auth-modal.jsx:263` | Remember Me not wired to backend | Pass `remember` flag to NextAuth `signIn()`; JWT callback sets `maxAge` |
| H7 | `auth.js` | No provider account linking | Support connecting multiple OAuth providers to same user account |
| H8 | `use-email-check.js`, `use-username-check.js` | No enumeration attack protection | Rate limit check endpoints per IP (5-10/min); consider always returning "available" |
| H9 | Shell, app-layout, dashboard | `MOCK_USER` objects hardcoded | Fetch from authenticated session via `useSession()` / NextAuth context |
| H10 | `contact.jsx` | No server-side form validation | Server must validate all fields, sanitize HTML, check CAPTCHA token |

